# Basic File System Commands

## ls
Lists files and directories.
```bash
ls -l
ls -a
```

## cd
Changes the current directory.
```bash
cd /etc
cd ..
```

## pwd
Shows the current directory.
```bash
pwd
```

## mkdir
Creates directories.
```bash
mkdir test_directory
```

## rm
Removes files and directories.
```bash
rm file.txt
rm -r test_directory
```
